{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Scope decision (user-approved): the comment-diff seam alone removes only ~245 LOC (1545->1301), which cannot reach the AC's <800 target. Expanding to the FULL per-concern split along the existing logical seams: comment-diff -> outbound_comments.py (done), field-diff -> outbound_fields.py, link-diff -> outbound_links.py. outbound_differ.py becomes the orchestrator (compute_outbound_mutations + OutboundDiffConfig) + a re-export facade so outbound_differ.<name> keeps resolving for the test suite (zero test churn except the compute_outbound_mutations signature migration). This MEETS the original <800 AC + removes the allowlist entry."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782688268794918001,"uuid":"bf86c648-0afd-4fa3-9362-3ed9010d81ce"}